element.name: Firefly series - #1 - Firefly by AbbeyAckbar, Traditional Cache (2/1.5)

p.b: Never heard of Firefly? Here's why

description.p: Firefly is a space western tv series created by writer and director Joss Whedon. It premiered in the United States and Canada on the Fox network on Sept. 20, 2002 & a whole 3 months and 14 episodes later (only 11 of which were aired), the show was cancelled, and that is where the story should have ended, but it didn't.

long-description.p: The ratings for the show were low (averaging only 4.7 MILLION viewers per episode!! and was 98th in the Nielsen Ratings) and Gail Berman of Fox was quoted in a national publication admitting that some of the problems with Firefly's ratings could be attributed to the way Fox had handled the program. The episodes were not aired in the order that the creators had intended. Most notably, the 2hr episode 'Serenity' was intended to be the pilot episode, as it contained most of the character introductions and back-story. However, Fox decided that 'Serenity' was not a suitable pilot, and so the second episode, 'The Train Job', was rushed into production to become the pilot episode.
Following huge fan support campaigns after the show was cancelled, Whedon and Universal Pictures went on to produce a film based on the series, called 'Serenity' shown in cinemas worldwide in 2005.

We have created this Firefly series out of our love of the show and its' characters. There are 11 caches in the series. Firstly the 'Firefly' cache, which is an introduction to the show. Then there is a cache created around each member of the Firefly crew and finally there's a bonus cache, the 'Serenity' cache.
Below you'll find a list of the main characters in Firefly, each with their own picture link to that character's cache page (as they get published :) ).

Obviously you don’t have to have seen either the tv show or the movie to find these caches but there are a few Firefly/Serenity references throughout the caches for fellow Browncoats out there, and although you may never get to see a single Firefly episode or the movie, Serenity, we hope you enjoy the Firefly caches and the locations they bring you to.
To all you Browncoat Geocachers out there....well...I don't believe there's a power in the verse could stop you from finding these gorram caches! and remember - can't stop the signal : )
The series is set in the year 2517, and follows the adventures of the renegade crew of Serenity, a "Firefly-class" spaceship.

It is a future where the only 2 surviving superpowers, the United States and China, fused to form the central federal government, called the Alliance, resulting in the fusion of the two cultures as well. The captain of Serenity, Malcolm "Mal" Reynolds, is the veteran of a war of resistance against "The Alliance"—an organization that attempted to achieve the unification of all mankind under a single imperial government.

The ship was named after the Battle of Serenity Valley, where the characters Mal and Zoe fought as Independents (aka Browncoats) against the Alliance. The battle was part of the Unification War, a failed attempt by the outlying worlds to resist the Alliance's assertion of control. The Battle of Serenity Valley is widely considered the loss which sealed the fate of the Independents. Throughout the series, the Alliance is shown to govern the star system through an organization of "core" planets, following its success in forcibly unifying all the colonies under a single government.

Mal now owns the small Firefly-class starship ‘Serenity’. In one of the episodes, titled "Out of Gas", it is revealed that Mal bought the spaceship Serenity to continue living beyond Alliance control. Much of the crew's work consists of cargo runs and performing various other tasks—legal or otherwise—to scrape together a living for himself and his crew.

Featuring a blend of elements from science fiction and western genres, the show depicts mankind's future in a way that is uncharacteristic of many sci-fi shows. The brilliant dialogue and interplay between characters is central to the plot of the show, resulting in a story that is alternately serious and humorous and brilliant to watch.

tr.td: Captain Malcolm Reynolds "Mal" is the owner of Serenity.
Zoe is second-in-command onboard Serenity, a loyal wartime friend of Mal, and the wife of Wash.
Wash is Serenity's pilot and the Husband of Zoe.
Inara is a highly regarded, registered Companion, who is of the highest social standing.
Jayne is hired muscle (but if anyone asks, he's in charge of public relations : ) ).

Kaylee is the ship's mechanic.
(The Kaylee cache is currently active. Click on the image to the right to visit this cache page.)
Simon is the ship's doctor and brother of River.
Derrial Book is a Shepherd (a preacher).

long-description.p: The cache is located near the newly built CCD (Convention Centre Dublin).

The centre is due to open 1st Sept 2010. The CCD is Ireland's new world-class, purpose-built international conference and event venue. It is comprised of 5 levels of rooms with capacity ranging from 10 - 4000 people. A suitable place for this cache as Firefly/Serenity & other sci-fi cons continue to be held around the world for fans of the shows.
Please be extra stealthy when retrieving and replacing the cache to prevent it from getting muggled.
I've uploaded a spoiler photo of the cache location to make things easier.
This cache is definately recommended at night for easier retrieval.

marquee.strong: Congratulations to Fitzet on the FTF!

#1123....20.00...Must have a look at the series and film sometime....not expecting that size container though...busy around area with festival on....TFTC...

2010-06-05T19:00:00Z : Write note by Fitzet
Dropped off the Rembrandt Geocoin which is on its way to Amsterdam.

2010-06-05T19:00:00Z : Found it by Fitzet
Our very first FTF and our 170th!
Needed a lot of distraction activity from the littlest Fitz running races to and from the crane but big Fitz slipped it out. Very proudly pinned on the FTF badge! In Nightwatch geocoin. Out FTF Badge.
SL TFTC
PS Firefly is one of my favourite sci-fi series - thrilled to see a caching series named after it!
